History of /dev/random in OpenBSD


apr 1996 - mickey - imports kernel random driver from ted ts'o

aug 1996 - dm/provos/deraadt - become convinced /dev/random
                   is a low-availability interface (not up to the task)

dec 1996 - dm/provos - arc4random() in libc is born


